HOUSE BILL 1036
E4, E2 EMERGENCY BILL 6lr3564
By: Delegate Bartlett
Introduced and read first time: February 9, 2026
Assigned to: Judiciary
A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Office of the Attorney General – Independent Investigations Division – Federal
3 Law Enforcement or Immigration Enforcement
4 FOR the purpose of requiring the Independent Investigations Division of the Office of the
5 Attorney General to investigate the death of a person that occurs in connection with
6 an interaction with federal law enforcement or federal immigration enforcement;
7 requiring the Division to submit a certain report at a certain time; requiring the
8 Attorney General to prosecute a certain case under certain circumstances; and
9 generally relating to the Independent Investigations Division.
10 BY adding to
11 Article – State Government
12 Section 6–605
13 Annotated Code of Maryland
14 (2021 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
15 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
16 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
17 Article – State Government
18 6–605.
19 (A) IN THIS SECTION, “SERIOUS PHYSICAL INJURY” HAS THE MEANING
20 STATED IN § 3–201 OF THE CRIMINAL LAW ARTICLE.
21 (B) IF A PERSON DIES OR SUSTAINS SERIOUS PHYSICAL INJURY IN
22 CONNECTION WITH AN INTERACTION WITH FEDERAL LAW ENFORCEMENT OR
23 FEDERAL IMMIGRATION ENFORCEMENT, THE DIVISION SHALL INVESTIGATE THE
24 DEATH OR SERIOUS PHYSICAL INJURY.
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
[Brackets] indicate matter deleted from exist in g l aw . *hb1036*

2 HOUSE BILL 1036
1 (C) AFTER CONDUCTING AN INVESTIGATION UNDER SUBSECTION (B) OF
2 THIS SECTION, THE DIVISION SHALL SUBMIT A REPORT TO THE GOVERNOR AND, IN
3 ACCORDANCE WITH § 2–1257 OF THIS ARTICLE, THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY SETTING
4 FORTH THE FINDINGS OF THE INVESTIGATION.
5 (D) IF THE ATTORNEY GENERAL DETERMINES THAT AN INVESTIGATION
6 CONDUCTED UNDER SUBSECTION (B) OF THIS SECTION PROVIDES SUFFICIENT
7 GROUNDS FOR PROSECUTION OF A FEDERAL LAW ENFORCEMENT OFFICER OR A
8 FEDERAL IMMIGRATION ENFORCEMENT OFFICER FOR THE COMMISSION OF A
9 CRIME, THE ATTORNEY GENERAL SHALL PROSECUTE THE CASE.
10 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act is an emergency
11 measure, is necessary for the immediate preservation of the public health or safety, has
12 been passed by a yea and nay vote supported by three–fifths of all the members elected to
13 each of the two Houses of the General Assembly, and shall take effect from the date it is
14 enacted.

